      <hedline>
        <hl1>Compassion First</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Vincente Garcia-Delgado letter on June 19 article holds Mayor Rudolph W Giuliani should have acted sooner to enroll poor in Medicaid</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I applaud Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani's plan aggressively to seek out poor children and adults to enroll in Medicaid (news analysis, June 19), but does he realize how much collective suffering, aggravation and anxiety would have been spared had he empathized sooner?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I applaud Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani's plan aggressively to seek out poor children and adults to enroll in Medicaid (news analysis, June 19), but does he realize how much collective suffering, aggravation and anxiety would have been spared had he empathized sooner?</p>
        <p>Compassion is an essential element of enlightened leadership, and our leaders should be expected to exercise it regardless of their own personal experiences.</p>
        <p>VICENTE GARCIA-DELGADO  New York, June 20, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a lawyer.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
